1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,000
We're not going running or doing yoga.

2
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,400
We're going swimming.

3
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:09,760
No, Win.

4
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:10,920
Don't.

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:12,840
If one day you still feel scared,

6
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:13,960
even knowing it's risky,

7
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,440
that's the day you realize
you're in love with that person.

8
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:19,920
A superstar like Win Pawee dating
a superstar like me…

9
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,960
it's still more suitable than
dating an extra like you.

10
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,760
May and I aren't anything anymore.

11
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,200
- We broke up.
- You don't have to explain.

12
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:28,240
We're not anything anyway.

13
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:30,600
Are you really living with Wanneung?

14
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:32,120
That's her bag, right?

15
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:33,320
Take it out.

16
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:35,000
Wanneung is staying here.

17
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,360
Wanneung and I…

18
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,320
we're in relationship.

19
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,560
We're dating.

20
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,320
Win.

21
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:57,920
Don't lie to me.

22
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:00,640
I don't believe you.

23
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,720
That's your right.

24
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:11,240
I have no right to force you
to believe it.

25
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:22,880
Meedee.

26
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,200
One day you'll realize

27
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,640
that you're wrong.

28
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,320
What is this, Win?

29
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,280
I'm so confused.

30
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,120
It's...

31
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,440
It's a ring...

32
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,400
A ring...

33
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,800
Why?

34
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:11,320
Can I have it back first?

35
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,560
Wanneung, it...

36
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,200
You jerk.

37
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,720
What do you think I am?

38
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:42,000
How could you toy
with my feelings like this?

39
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,000
Why are you so upset?

40
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,280
You have no idea how much
I love Wanneung.

41
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,400
I've always loved her

42
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,200
and waited for her.

43
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,320
I've been chasing after her,

44
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,320
but she never softened
toward me even once.

45
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,800
And now some random idiot

46
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,680
just came and took her away.

47
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,920
Don't call Win an idiot.

48
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,880
Watch your mouth.

49
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,400
Win is a superstar in Thailand.

50
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,920
So what if she's a superstar?

51
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,120
A superstar is still a person,
isn't she?

52
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:29,320
In the end, she still took
what belonged to me.

53
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,560
Shameless.

54
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:35,320
What's so great about her anyway?

55
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,640
Why does everyone love her so much?

56
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:40,240
Don't call Wanneung "that."

57
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,320
What are you doing?

58
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,200
Wanneung.

59
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,880
Wanneung, are you asleep?

60
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,600
Can you open the door for me?

61
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,880
Wanneung, are you awake?

62
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,560
What are you doing here?

63
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,080
I'm going to sleep.

64
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,320
You haven't eaten since evening.

65
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:02,320
Do you want to come eat?
I made food for you.

66
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:05,320
It's already late.
I'm going to bed.

67
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,280
I'm sorry.

68
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,480
Did you get hurt anywhere?

69
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:17,120
I didn't mean to.
Are you okay?

70
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,040
Win.

71
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,680
You lied to me.

72
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,760
How long were you going
to keep lying?

73
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,240
Wanneung.

74
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,400
I've never lied to you.

75
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,760
It's so beautiful, Win.

76
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,560
I went through all this effort
to prepare everything.

77
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:58,200
If you hadn't come down,
I would've been really sad.

78
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,840
Well, I did come down, didn't I?

79
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:03,880
Then please, go ahead.

80
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,240
Sure.

81
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,840
Thank you.

82
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,200
You're welcome.

83
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:32,760
Beautiful customer,
are you ready for dinner?

84
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,440
I'm ready.

85
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:37,920
Then let's start
with the appetizer.

86
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,000
Okay.

87
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,280
Just a moment.

88
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,400
Sure.

89
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,960
Your appetizer is served.

90
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:00,960
Can I open it now?

91
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,400
Of course.

92
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:26,160
A Echinopsis colochlora.

93
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,000
Why are you giving this to me?

94
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,520
Well...

95
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,280
You once gave me one,

96
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,200
so I wanted to give one back.

97
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:36,480
Now your dream is about to come true.

98
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:39,200
You're going to become
the star you've always dreamed of.

99
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,040
Thank you.

100
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,840
The appetizer is here.

101
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,480
Shall we move on to
the main course?

102
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:59,760
Please bring it out, Chef.
Our guest is hungry.

103
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,120
Just a moment.

104
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,120
Sure.

105
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,760
Here it comes.

106
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,920
This is the main course.

107
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:41,120
The main course?

108
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,840
All right.

109
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,920
I'm going to open it now.

110
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,560
Go ahead.

111
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:54,960
What could it be?

112
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,920
A ring.

113
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,920
A ring.

114
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,360
A ring.

115
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,800
A ring.

116
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,960
You...

117
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:19,040
Don't you like steak?

118
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,880
No, I like it.

119
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,360
Then...

120
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,840
Enjoy your meal.

121
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,400
Okay.

122
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,960
Since you've already packed,

123
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,440
I figured you could move
into this room with me.

124
00:12:58,720 --> 00:12:59,960
How could that be?

125
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,240
We're not even anything.

126
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,920
Please.

127
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,760
I mean...

128
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,720
I'm scared of ghosts.

129
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,240
Can you sleep with me?

130
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,320
If you're scared of ghosts,
wear a Buddha amulet.

131
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,400
What do you take me for?

132
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,760
A crazy person?

133
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:24,840
Where are you going?

134
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:28,600
I'm going to brush my teeth
and then go to bed.

135
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:29,760
I'm coming with you.

136
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,560
Brush my teeth for me.

137
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:48,880
If we live together like this,
we'll have to fight over the bathroom.

138
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,400
So troublesome.

139
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,160
Hey.

140
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:04,640
Aren't you going to dip
the toothbrush in water?

141
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,960
No.

142
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
It's sticky.

143
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,160
Is this okay?

144
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:19,920
Do it properly.

145
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:23,640
Brush it nice and clean.

146
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,120
You... Win.

147
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:30,240
I can't see.

148
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,800
Win.

149
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,120
Brush yours too.

150
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:42,000
Brush mine too.

151
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,120
I'm not good at doing it.

152
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,120
Here, I'll hold it for you.

153
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,640
If you want it, just ask me.

154
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:00,800
I smell bad.
I just finished cooking.

155
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:02,680
Then I'll take another shower.

156
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,840
Do you want to shower together?

157
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:05,760
No.

158
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:08,840
I just showered.
Why would I shower again?

159
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,160
Okay.

160
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:17,480
I'll shower by myself then.

161
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:25,360
Ow, the water splashed.

162
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,480
Win.

163
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:29,800
- What are you doing, Win?
- I turned the water too strong.

164
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,120
Win, I'm all wet now.

165
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:35,280
- I told you to shower with me.
- Win, Win.

166
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,760
- Win.
- Wanneung.

167
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,600
Win.

168
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,440
You're soaked now,
so you have to shower again.

169
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:44,400
I just took a shower.

170
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:45,760
But you're already wet.

171
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,640
Win.

172
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:51,200
I asked you nicely,
but you wouldn't shower with me.

173
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:15,560
Wanneung finally
has a girlfriend now.

174
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:16,920
Excuse me.

175
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,400
Are you Wanneung?

176
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,960
You're getting really famous now,

177
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,200
Win.

178
00:17:44,175 --> 00:17:48,455
Why would Win date some kid
who's clearly not as good as me?

179
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:52,055
I'm perfect
and a superstar loved nationwide.

180
00:17:52,135 --> 00:17:53,935
This is about love,

181
00:17:54,335 --> 00:17:55,775
not a job application.

182
00:17:56,215 --> 00:17:57,375
It's not about who's better,

183
00:17:57,495 --> 00:17:58,695
prettier,

184
00:17:58,775 --> 00:17:59,935
or more perfect.

185
00:18:00,295 --> 00:18:01,295
Love...

186
00:18:01,495 --> 00:18:04,015
is simply loving or not loving.

187
00:18:04,455 --> 00:18:06,335
That's all there is.

188
00:18:06,575 --> 00:18:08,415
But that little kid Wanneung,

189
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,015
she doesn't love you.

190
00:18:11,015 --> 00:18:12,095
That's right.

191
00:18:12,375 --> 00:18:14,575
We're in the same boat, May.

192
00:18:56,975 --> 00:18:58,375
Wake up.

193
00:18:59,695 --> 00:19:01,495
Win.

194
00:19:01,815 --> 00:19:04,215
Can I sleep a little longer?

195
00:19:04,415 --> 00:19:07,015
My alarm hasn't gone off yet.

196
00:20:19,095 --> 00:20:21,335
(Will you be my girlfriend?)

197
00:20:35,775 --> 00:20:37,015
Wanneung.

198
00:20:37,855 --> 00:20:39,255
Why are you crying?

199
00:20:43,855 --> 00:20:45,175
I thought...

200
00:20:45,255 --> 00:20:47,855
what you said in front of
May and Meedee

201
00:20:47,895 --> 00:20:50,255
was just pretend.

202
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:54,375
I thought you weren't serious
about me.

203
00:20:54,455 --> 00:20:57,415
And what happened between us

204
00:20:57,455 --> 00:20:59,015
was just...

205
00:20:59,055 --> 00:21:01,975
a silly dream
I had all by myself.

206
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,095
Wanneung.

207
00:21:05,815 --> 00:21:07,295
I'm sorry.

208
00:21:07,575 --> 00:21:09,575
I'm really sorry.

209
00:21:12,735 --> 00:21:15,535
I didn't mean to make you
overthink things.

210
00:21:15,695 --> 00:21:17,055
I just...

211
00:21:17,095 --> 00:21:20,055
wanted it to be
a special moment for us.

212
00:21:20,695 --> 00:21:23,175
That's why I asked
for the ring back first.

213
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:24,815
Actually...

214
00:21:26,175 --> 00:21:29,055
I wanted to ask you
to be my girlfriend since last night.

215
00:21:29,095 --> 00:21:31,095
And I wanted to do it
in front of everyone, but...

216
00:21:36,055 --> 00:21:37,415
I didn't dare.

217
00:21:41,215 --> 00:21:42,655
Just now...

218
00:21:43,255 --> 00:21:45,255
what did you say?

219
00:21:50,415 --> 00:21:52,215
Nothing. I didn't say anything.

220
00:21:53,375 --> 00:21:55,535
Please, Win.

221
00:21:55,575 --> 00:21:57,615
Say it again, please.

222
00:21:57,655 --> 00:21:59,175
Can I hear it one more time?

223
00:21:59,215 --> 00:22:01,335
Just say it clearly.

224
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:03,415
- Please.
- You already heard it.

225
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:05,175
What did you want to ask me?

226
00:22:06,775 --> 00:22:09,415
Please, I'm begging you.

227
00:22:10,575 --> 00:22:11,655
Please.

228
00:22:12,335 --> 00:22:13,935
Please, Win.

229
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:21,655
(Will you be my girlfriend?)

230
00:22:22,575 --> 00:22:24,055
What does it mean?

231
00:22:24,095 --> 00:22:25,295
I...

232
00:22:25,775 --> 00:22:27,135
can't read it.

233
00:22:27,135 --> 00:22:30,055
I'd rather hear it
from your mouth.

234
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:32,735
Just read the sign yourself.

235
00:22:32,775 --> 00:22:34,735
It's not hard. Here.

236
00:22:39,175 --> 00:22:40,975
Where's the sign?

237
00:22:41,015 --> 00:22:43,175
I can't find it.

238
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:44,735
Just say it for me.

239
00:22:44,735 --> 00:22:48,535
- I can't see it. Where is it?
- You're teasing me.

240
00:22:48,535 --> 00:22:49,735
Wanneung.

241
00:22:57,655 --> 00:22:58,975
Will you be my girlfriend?

242
00:23:09,015 --> 00:23:10,455
Yes.

243
00:23:24,215 --> 00:23:26,575
Wanneung finally
has a girlfriend now.

244
00:23:26,615 --> 00:23:29,535
Wanneung finally
has a girlfriend now.

245
00:23:29,735 --> 00:23:31,975
My head is spinning.

246
00:23:32,335 --> 00:23:33,895
I feel dizzy.

247
00:23:36,895 --> 00:23:38,255
Win of Wanneung,

248
00:23:38,255 --> 00:23:41,055
you're the sweetest.

249
00:23:46,975 --> 00:23:50,255
(20/03/2026) (Day 1)

250
00:23:50,295 --> 00:23:53,215
(20/03/2026) (Day 1)

251
00:24:18,775 --> 00:24:19,775
Hey.

252
00:24:23,855 --> 00:24:25,295
About last night...

253
00:24:25,335 --> 00:24:26,775
You don't have to take it seriously.

254
00:24:29,055 --> 00:24:30,695
We were both drunk.

255
00:24:30,815 --> 00:24:32,615
Just treat it
like a one- night stand.

256
00:24:33,655 --> 00:24:35,535
Are you joking?

257
00:24:36,175 --> 00:24:39,175
I'm the one
who should be saying that.

258
00:24:45,495 --> 00:24:47,495
And don't go around telling people

259
00:24:47,575 --> 00:24:50,855
that you had a one- night stand
with a superstar like me.

260
00:25:06,135 --> 00:25:08,295
Hey, calm down.

261
00:25:19,695 --> 00:25:20,895
What would you like?

262
00:25:20,895 --> 00:25:22,175
Please go ahead and order.

263
00:25:22,255 --> 00:25:24,895
Yes, I'd like one soft- serve ice cream.

264
00:25:24,895 --> 00:25:27,055
Sure, one soft- serve to go.

265
00:25:27,055 --> 00:25:28,095
Yes.

266
00:25:28,655 --> 00:25:30,575
- Let's go over there.
- What should we eat?

267
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,135
Hey, hey, hey!

268
00:25:32,175 --> 00:25:33,415
Isn't that Wanneung?

269
00:25:33,455 --> 00:25:34,535
Hey, you're right.

270
00:25:34,575 --> 00:25:36,015
Let's go check it out.

271
00:25:37,895 --> 00:25:39,055
Excuse me.

272
00:25:39,095 --> 00:25:41,095
Are you Wanneung?

273
00:25:41,855 --> 00:25:44,655
You know who I am?

274
00:25:45,455 --> 00:25:46,975
I'm a fan of Win.

275
00:25:47,015 --> 00:25:50,975
When I saw the news last night
that you two live together, I almost screamed.

276
00:25:51,175 --> 00:25:52,615
Um...

277
00:25:52,655 --> 00:25:53,815
Did you come alone?

278
00:25:53,855 --> 00:25:55,695
Didn't Win come with you?

279
00:25:58,775 --> 00:26:00,895
Yes, I'm alone.

280
00:26:01,175 --> 00:26:03,015
Oh.

281
00:26:03,295 --> 00:26:06,495
So are you and Win
really dating?

282
00:26:06,535 --> 00:26:07,935
Is it true?

283
00:26:11,815 --> 00:26:13,495
Oh, it's okay.

284
00:26:13,495 --> 00:26:16,375
A BL fan like me
already believes it's real.

285
00:26:16,415 --> 00:26:18,935
I've even created a hashtag
for you two.

286
00:26:19,255 --> 00:26:20,655
Win–Wanneung.

287
00:26:20,815 --> 00:26:23,455
- It's way cooler than "WinMay."
- True.

288
00:26:23,495 --> 00:26:24,935
Can I take a photo with you?

289
00:26:24,975 --> 00:26:26,175
Sure.

290
00:26:27,375 --> 00:26:28,975
One, two, three.

291
00:26:29,255 --> 00:26:31,375
- Can you do a saranghaeyo pose?
- Sure.

292
00:26:31,375 --> 00:26:33,015
One, two, three.

293
00:26:33,095 --> 00:26:34,535
So cute.

294
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:37,415
Thank you. You're so sweet.

295
00:26:37,455 --> 00:26:40,055
- Thank you.
- Bye- bye.

296
00:26:40,055 --> 00:26:41,735
Bye- bye.

297
00:26:42,415 --> 00:26:44,055
So cute.

298
00:27:01,695 --> 00:27:03,415
I'll wait in the car.

299
00:27:05,975 --> 00:27:08,295
You're getting really famous now,

300
00:27:08,455 --> 00:27:09,975
Win.

301
00:27:13,495 --> 00:27:14,495
Win.

302
00:27:14,535 --> 00:27:17,415
I'm getting famous now,
and fans are asking for photos.

303
00:27:17,415 --> 00:27:19,895
I'm excited
and don't know how to act.

304
00:27:19,935 --> 00:27:21,535
You'll get used to it.

305
00:27:21,575 --> 00:27:23,575
And...

306
00:27:23,655 --> 00:27:25,335
Here’s your ice cream.

307
00:27:25,495 --> 00:27:27,615
Thank you.

308
00:27:27,895 --> 00:27:29,575
Let me see.

309
00:27:32,455 --> 00:27:34,055
You bought this many?

310
00:27:34,095 --> 00:27:36,095
How am I supposed to finish them?

311
00:27:36,295 --> 00:27:37,295
Well...

312
00:27:37,295 --> 00:27:41,015
I didn’t know which flavor you like,
so I bought them all.

313
00:27:41,015 --> 00:27:44,135
You were chatting with your fans
like old friends,

314
00:27:44,135 --> 00:27:45,775
and I didn’t want to interrupt.

315
00:27:46,615 --> 00:27:47,615
Okay.

316
00:27:48,335 --> 00:27:51,535
Then I’ll finish every flavor.

317
00:27:51,775 --> 00:27:53,255
All of them?

318
00:27:59,855 --> 00:28:01,855
- This one is...
- So good.

319
00:28:07,295 --> 00:28:09,575
You’re eating so messily.

320
00:28:10,055 --> 00:28:13,015
You can slow down.
No one’s taking it from you.

321
00:28:13,695 --> 00:28:16,455
It’s melting, so I’m eating fast.

322
00:28:16,495 --> 00:28:18,175
Alright, go ahead.

323
00:28:18,215 --> 00:28:19,735
Thank you.

324
00:28:21,055 --> 00:28:22,255
This one.

325
00:28:25,895 --> 00:28:27,455
Sorry, Win.

326
00:28:27,495 --> 00:28:29,215
I’m sorry.

327
00:28:34,975 --> 00:28:37,615
From now on,
I’m charging you.

328
00:28:37,655 --> 00:28:38,975
One kiss, one thousand baht.

329
00:28:41,335 --> 00:28:43,095
If that’s the case,

330
00:28:43,775 --> 00:28:46,015
I’ll pay my whole bank account.

331
00:28:49,175 --> 00:28:51,135
Please, Win.

332
00:28:51,175 --> 00:28:53,855
Someone might see us.

333
00:28:54,655 --> 00:28:55,975
I can't hold back anymore.

334
00:28:56,015 --> 00:28:59,495
Or are you not afraid
of people seeing you with me?

335
00:29:02,015 --> 00:29:04,095
Getting to kiss my girlfriend

336
00:29:05,135 --> 00:29:06,495
makes me fearless.

337
00:29:09,655 --> 00:29:12,215
- Where’s my spoon?
- You dropped it.

338
00:29:13,295 --> 00:29:15,615
All the flavors are mixed up now.

339
00:29:17,055 --> 00:29:18,895
Want a new cup?
I’ll open one.

340
00:29:21,095 --> 00:29:23,775
- Want some?
- No, it’s okay. I’ll feed you.

341
00:29:24,135 --> 00:29:25,535
Alright.

342
00:29:26,775 --> 00:29:29,415
After this,
you still have acting class.

343
00:29:29,455 --> 00:29:30,575
Don’t forget.

344
00:29:35,175 --> 00:29:37,015
It’s really delicious.

345
00:29:37,295 --> 00:29:38,335
Is it good?

346
00:29:38,895 --> 00:29:42,015
The plane is landing.

347
00:29:46,415 --> 00:29:47,455
Okay.

348
00:29:47,455 --> 00:29:49,135
I’ll take a look.

349
00:29:56,655 --> 00:29:58,375
Hey, Wanneung.

350
00:29:58,895 --> 00:30:00,495
Why didn’t you tell me?

351
00:30:01,335 --> 00:30:03,415
Tell you about what,
P’Waanwaan?

352
00:30:04,415 --> 00:30:06,655
Don’t pretend you don’t know.

353
00:30:06,775 --> 00:30:07,855
Right now,

354
00:30:07,895 --> 00:30:11,415
the internet is full of news
that you’re living with Win.

355
00:30:13,215 --> 00:30:15,215
You haven’t checked X, right?

356
00:30:15,575 --> 00:30:18,135
But do you know
what’s even more shocking?

357
00:30:18,415 --> 00:30:19,535
Right now...

358
00:30:19,575 --> 00:30:21,575
WinMay’s fanbase

359
00:30:21,615 --> 00:30:24,095
is cursing you so hard
it’s trending.

360
00:30:24,615 --> 00:30:26,055
And you know what?

361
00:30:26,175 --> 00:30:27,855
Since this morning,

362
00:30:27,895 --> 00:30:30,015
I haven’t stopped getting calls
from reporters,

363
00:30:30,055 --> 00:30:31,935
my ears are about to explode.

364
00:30:33,815 --> 00:30:35,415
Well...

365
00:30:35,455 --> 00:30:36,855
Do you want to answer them yourself?

366
00:30:38,135 --> 00:30:39,415
Always causing trouble.

367
00:30:40,095 --> 00:30:41,095
Yes, P’Waanwaan.

368
00:30:50,695 --> 00:30:52,655
Did P’Waanwaan scold you?

369
00:30:53,095 --> 00:30:54,535
Yeah.

370
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:56,655
What should I do?

371
00:30:56,695 --> 00:31:00,135
If P’Waanwaan gets upset
and tears up my contract,

372
00:31:00,175 --> 00:31:02,415
then my path to becoming a superstar

373
00:31:02,455 --> 00:31:04,975
will end
before it even begins.

374
00:31:05,015 --> 00:31:06,495
Actually...

375
00:31:06,535 --> 00:31:08,935
if P’Waanwaan tears up the contract,

376
00:31:08,935 --> 00:31:10,855
it might be better for you.

377
00:31:12,495 --> 00:31:13,695
Why, Gam?

378
00:31:16,375 --> 00:31:17,935
Nothing, it’s nothing.

379
00:31:19,175 --> 00:31:20,175
Hey.

380
00:31:20,215 --> 00:31:21,775
P’Waanwaan asked me
to give this to you.

381
00:31:22,215 --> 00:31:25,935
She said she secretly got it from the client
for our casting, so you could rehearse first.

382
00:31:26,335 --> 00:31:27,775
Try memorizing it.

383
00:31:28,575 --> 00:31:31,175
If P’Waanwaan comes back and you still can’t recite it,

384
00:31:31,175 --> 00:31:32,815
you’ll get scolded again.

385
00:31:33,495 --> 00:31:35,175
Thanks, Gam.

386
00:31:35,615 --> 00:31:36,615
Let’s go.

387
00:31:58,175 --> 00:32:01,655
But tonight
she’s going to do the same thing again.

388
00:32:01,655 --> 00:32:03,735
Rushing over to see
a director like P’Tong,

389
00:32:03,735 --> 00:32:05,135
something must be wrong.

390
00:32:05,135 --> 00:32:06,775
I have nothing to say to you.

391
00:32:06,775 --> 00:32:08,055
But I do.

392
00:32:22,562 --> 00:32:23,802
I told you already.

393
00:32:23,802 --> 00:32:26,482
There’s nothing between us.
I don’t love her.

394
00:32:26,562 --> 00:32:28,482
Then why are you with her?

395
00:32:28,602 --> 00:32:30,562
Because from the beginning I knew

396
00:32:30,602 --> 00:32:33,282
she could help me reach my dream.

397
00:32:33,282 --> 00:32:36,282
I’ll do anything to get what I want.

398
00:32:36,282 --> 00:32:37,402
That’s all.

399
00:32:37,642 --> 00:32:40,082
My dream matters most.

400
00:32:41,482 --> 00:32:43,162
Are you using her?

401
00:32:43,202 --> 00:32:44,562
If she’s smart,

402
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:46,282
she’ll see through it.

403
00:32:46,322 --> 00:32:48,362
She wouldn’t let me
use her so easily.

404
00:32:48,362 --> 00:32:50,122
But if she’s stupid...

405
00:32:52,842 --> 00:32:53,842
P’Waanwaan.

406
00:32:53,842 --> 00:32:56,442
I rushed back from out of town

407
00:32:56,522 --> 00:32:59,002
just to deal with this news for you.

408
00:33:16,402 --> 00:33:18,082
Aren't you affected at all?

409
00:33:18,322 --> 00:33:19,882
with news like this coming out

410
00:33:21,682 --> 00:33:24,242
I rushed back from out of town

411
00:33:24,242 --> 00:33:25,762
to deal with the news for you.

412
00:33:26,282 --> 00:33:28,362
Reporters have been calling nonstop.

413
00:33:28,522 --> 00:33:29,962
Forget it, Tom.

414
00:33:30,242 --> 00:33:32,162
Just think of it as…

415
00:33:32,202 --> 00:33:34,602
building hype before the movie launches.

416
00:33:35,282 --> 00:33:36,922
Hype my ass.

417
00:33:37,722 --> 00:33:39,242
The one who should be in the news

418
00:33:39,282 --> 00:33:40,962
is May, not Wanneung.

419
00:33:41,402 --> 00:33:43,762
News like this only hurts.

420
00:33:43,922 --> 00:33:44,922
Oh…

421
00:33:46,882 --> 00:33:48,122
(Wanneung)

422
00:33:51,722 --> 00:33:53,042
Hello, Wanneung.

423
00:33:53,882 --> 00:33:56,322
Win, I just finished my acting class.

424
00:33:56,522 --> 00:33:58,522
Why did you finish so early today?

425
00:33:58,682 --> 00:34:00,922
Want me to pick you up?
We can grab something to eat.

426
00:34:01,042 --> 00:34:02,202
It’s okay.

427
00:34:02,482 --> 00:34:03,962
Actually…

428
00:34:04,322 --> 00:34:06,402
Gam asked me to have dinner with her.

429
00:34:06,442 --> 00:34:09,082
She said she’s stressed about something.

430
00:34:09,082 --> 00:34:11,042
So I thought I’d keep her company.

431
00:34:11,242 --> 00:34:12,522
Oh really?

432
00:34:12,602 --> 00:34:14,842
What time will you finish?
Should I pick you up?

433
00:34:15,322 --> 00:34:16,562
I’m not sure yet.

434
00:34:16,602 --> 00:34:18,802
I’ll call you later and let you know.

435
00:34:20,602 --> 00:34:21,962
What a pity.

436
00:34:21,962 --> 00:34:24,322
We won’t get to have dinner together.

437
00:34:25,002 --> 00:34:28,202
Then how about late- night rice porridge?

438
00:34:28,402 --> 00:34:29,882
Win.

439
00:34:31,122 --> 00:34:32,762
I should go now.

440
00:34:32,802 --> 00:34:33,922
I’ll call you again.

441
00:34:33,922 --> 00:34:35,522
Okay.

442
00:34:42,642 --> 00:34:44,322
I’ll hang up first.

443
00:34:44,842 --> 00:34:46,642
Okay, see you.

444
00:34:55,162 --> 00:34:56,842
Isn’t this a bit too much, Win?

445
00:34:57,882 --> 00:34:59,322
You’re still here?

446
00:34:59,522 --> 00:35:01,082
I thought you’d gone home.

447
00:35:01,242 --> 00:35:02,682
How could I go home?

448
00:35:02,842 --> 00:35:04,282
You haven’t decided yet

449
00:35:04,362 --> 00:35:06,322
what to do about that news.

450
00:35:21,482 --> 00:35:24,842
(P’Tong Director)

451
00:35:26,322 --> 00:35:27,522
Hello, Win.

452
00:35:27,562 --> 00:35:28,562
I’m here to see P’Tong.

453
00:35:28,602 --> 00:35:31,802
- Please go right in. He’s waiting in the room.
- Thank you.

454
00:35:35,042 --> 00:35:37,562
Rushing over to see
a director like P’Tong,

455
00:35:37,722 --> 00:35:39,362
something must be wrong.

456
00:35:39,642 --> 00:35:41,122
P’Waanwaan.

457
00:35:41,162 --> 00:35:42,402
What are you doing here?

458
00:35:42,602 --> 00:35:43,762
What’s strange about it?

459
00:35:43,802 --> 00:35:45,842
Two of my artists are in his film.

460
00:35:45,842 --> 00:35:47,842
I just stopped by
to talk with the director.

461
00:35:47,842 --> 00:35:49,122
Nothing strange about that.

462
00:35:49,682 --> 00:35:51,162
Then I’ll excuse myself.

463
00:35:51,162 --> 00:35:52,202
Wait.

464
00:35:53,242 --> 00:35:54,722
We haven’t talked yet, Win.

465
00:35:55,442 --> 00:35:57,082
I have nothing to say to you.

466
00:35:57,122 --> 00:35:58,402
But I do.

467
00:35:59,002 --> 00:36:01,402
Are you dating Wanneung?

468
00:36:02,562 --> 00:36:03,562
Oh.

469
00:36:04,042 --> 00:36:05,682
Matching rings too.

470
00:36:09,402 --> 00:36:11,482
Is that all you wanted to say?

471
00:36:11,482 --> 00:36:13,482
Come on.

472
00:36:13,602 --> 00:36:15,522
You could be nicer to me.

473
00:36:15,562 --> 00:36:18,682
I used to be your manager.

474
00:36:19,042 --> 00:36:20,642
A manager who betrayed

475
00:36:20,802 --> 00:36:22,242
and blackmailed her own artist.

476
00:36:22,762 --> 00:36:24,442
After what you did,

477
00:36:24,722 --> 00:36:26,442
you’re lucky I didn’t file a report.

478
00:36:26,482 --> 00:36:29,002
Then why did you try
to tear up my contract first?

479
00:36:29,002 --> 00:36:31,122
I had to strike back somehow.

480
00:36:35,162 --> 00:36:37,002
Why are you living
in the same house as Win?

481
00:36:37,002 --> 00:36:39,002
Because from the start

482
00:36:39,042 --> 00:36:41,962
I knew she could help me
reach my dream.

483
00:36:42,002 --> 00:36:45,442
I’ll do anything
to get what I want.

484
00:36:45,482 --> 00:36:46,482
That’s all.

485
00:36:46,682 --> 00:36:49,602
My dream matters most.

486
00:36:49,642 --> 00:36:52,162
What? So you’re using Win?

487
00:36:52,162 --> 00:36:54,962
If she’s smart enough,
she’ll see through it.

488
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:57,122
She wouldn’t let me
use her that easily.

489
00:36:57,202 --> 00:37:00,482
But if she’s stupid,
then that’s not my problem.

490
00:37:01,882 --> 00:37:04,682
I never thought Wanneung
could be this vicious.

491
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:07,442
With that pretty face,
I thought she was innocent.

492
00:37:07,762 --> 00:37:11,122
I came to warn you
because I care about you.

493
00:37:25,842 --> 00:37:27,162
Hey, Gam.

494
00:37:27,322 --> 00:37:28,682
Calm down.

495
00:37:29,162 --> 00:37:30,442
What’s wrong?

496
00:37:30,962 --> 00:37:33,322
If something’s bothering you,
you can tell me.

497
00:37:50,802 --> 00:37:52,962
Have you seen this clip before?

498
00:38:04,402 --> 00:38:06,122
I’ve only seen it briefly.

499
00:38:06,362 --> 00:38:08,042
I didn’t pay attention back then.

500
00:38:08,082 --> 00:38:09,922
I didn’t think
it was this serious.

501
00:38:10,122 --> 00:38:11,602
It’s serious, right?

502
00:38:12,762 --> 00:38:14,322
Because of this leaked clip,

503
00:38:14,642 --> 00:38:17,042
Win got kicked out
of the entertainment industry.

504
00:38:18,722 --> 00:38:20,122
Then...

505
00:38:21,082 --> 00:38:23,002
why are you telling me this?

506
00:38:28,362 --> 00:38:29,442
Gam.

507
00:38:29,642 --> 00:38:31,202
What’s going on?

508
00:38:32,162 --> 00:38:34,042
The truth is...

509
00:38:36,562 --> 00:38:38,602
the investors are very serious about this.

510
00:38:38,642 --> 00:38:39,682
About the news…

511
00:38:39,722 --> 00:38:41,562
There’s really nothing to it, P’Tong.

512
00:38:41,602 --> 00:38:43,242
I just live
in the same house as Wanneung.

513
00:38:43,282 --> 00:38:45,562
I don’t see what the problem is.

514
00:38:45,602 --> 00:38:48,402
Maybe that’s the truth,
but right now…

515
00:38:48,442 --> 00:38:51,322
people online
have blown it way out of proportion.

516
00:38:53,482 --> 00:38:54,562
Listen to me.

517
00:38:55,922 --> 00:38:58,722
Wanneung’s role
isn’t the lead.

518
00:38:58,722 --> 00:39:00,682
It’s not even a standout role.

519
00:39:00,682 --> 00:39:02,322
So if we replace the actress,

520
00:39:02,362 --> 00:39:05,002
and the film can keep moving forward, I…

521
00:39:05,922 --> 00:39:08,642
…I think we need to do something…
P’Tong.

522
00:39:15,202 --> 00:39:16,842
I’ve made my decision.

523
00:39:27,242 --> 00:39:28,962
The truth is…

524
00:39:29,802 --> 00:39:32,242
the clip isn’t
what it looks like.

525
00:39:34,682 --> 00:39:37,202
P’Waanwaan staged the whole thing.

526
00:39:38,162 --> 00:39:41,362
Because she was angry
Win wanted to cancel the contract.

527
00:39:43,682 --> 00:39:44,882
No wonder.

528
00:39:44,882 --> 00:39:46,322
So that’s why.

529
00:39:46,722 --> 00:39:50,722
Win got so upset
when she found out

530
00:39:52,642 --> 00:39:55,722
I signed with P’Waanwaan.

531
00:39:58,362 --> 00:40:02,242
But tonight
she’s going to do the same thing again.

532
00:40:02,882 --> 00:40:06,362
She’ll do to May
what she did to Win.

533
00:40:07,642 --> 00:40:09,922
She wants to push me

534
00:40:10,242 --> 00:40:13,922
to become the female lead
in this film instead.

535
00:40:14,162 --> 00:40:15,562
Is it tonight, Gam?

536
00:40:16,082 --> 00:40:18,602
- Where?
- At P’Waanwaan’s condo.

537
00:40:18,642 --> 00:40:20,042
Eight o’clock.

538
00:40:21,682 --> 00:40:23,362
Gam, send me the location.

539
00:40:23,402 --> 00:40:24,482
Okay, okay.

540
00:40:24,482 --> 00:40:25,962
And the room number too.

541
00:40:29,362 --> 00:40:30,922
Could you go a little faster, driver?

542
00:40:31,962 --> 00:40:33,202
Thank you.

543
00:40:34,802 --> 00:40:36,042
Thank you.

544
00:41:00,882 --> 00:41:04,082
Whenever something urgent happens,
you never answer my calls, Win.

545
00:41:08,482 --> 00:41:09,922
Meedee.

546
00:41:15,362 --> 00:41:16,562
Hello, Meedee.

547
00:41:16,602 --> 00:41:18,162
I need your help.

548
00:41:18,642 --> 00:41:20,442
Send me the location right now.

549
00:41:20,922 --> 00:41:23,202
And don’t go in yet.
Wait for me.

550
00:41:57,842 --> 00:42:01,042
She can help me reach my dream.

551
00:42:01,082 --> 00:42:04,442
I’ll do anything
to get what I want.

552
00:42:04,482 --> 00:42:05,682
That’s all.

553
00:42:05,722 --> 00:42:09,242
My dream matters most.

554
00:42:17,682 --> 00:42:20,122
Without a keycard,
you really can’t go up.

555
00:42:20,242 --> 00:42:22,482
Please, could you help me?

556
00:42:23,722 --> 00:42:24,762
Please.

557
00:42:28,842 --> 00:42:31,682
Do you know P’Waanwaan?

558
00:42:32,362 --> 00:42:35,042
Yes, I do.
She’s an artist manager, right?

559
00:42:35,082 --> 00:42:36,122
Yes.

560
00:42:36,122 --> 00:42:38,642
I’m an actress.
Look at my face.

561
00:42:41,562 --> 00:42:44,162
P’Waanwaan isn’t feeling well.
She called me to help.

562
00:42:44,202 --> 00:42:45,842
Please let me go up.

563
00:42:46,042 --> 00:42:47,682
I need to check on her.

564
00:42:48,722 --> 00:42:50,762
You can come up with me.

565
00:42:54,322 --> 00:42:55,642
Trust me.

566
00:42:55,682 --> 00:42:58,842
If something happens to her,
you’ll be in trouble.

567
00:43:00,762 --> 00:43:02,322
Hurry.

568
00:43:02,322 --> 00:43:03,682
Please.

569
00:43:04,002 --> 00:43:05,242
Please.

570
00:43:08,882 --> 00:43:09,962
Miss,

571
00:43:09,962 --> 00:43:11,642
please calm down.

572
00:43:11,682 --> 00:43:13,082
Wait for me.

573
00:43:20,002 --> 00:43:21,242
What’s wrong?

574
00:43:21,562 --> 00:43:23,002
Ring the bell.

575
00:43:34,002 --> 00:43:35,042
Wanneung?

576
00:43:36,122 --> 00:43:37,402
What are you doing here?

577
00:43:39,602 --> 00:43:41,762
I’ll take my leave then,
P’Waanwaan.

578
00:43:46,442 --> 00:43:50,002
She said you weren’t feeling well,

579
00:43:50,042 --> 00:43:52,002
so you called her to come here.

580
00:43:57,002 --> 00:43:58,042
Wanneung.

581
00:43:58,042 --> 00:43:59,042
Wanneung.

582
00:43:59,122 --> 00:44:00,962
Stop, Wanneung.

583
00:44:05,842 --> 00:44:06,842
May.

584
00:44:07,002 --> 00:44:08,162
May.

585
00:44:11,202 --> 00:44:13,202
P’Waanwaan, what did you do to her?

586
00:44:13,322 --> 00:44:14,322
Do what?

587
00:44:14,522 --> 00:44:17,402
She was stressed because of the news,
so she came to talk to me.

588
00:44:17,642 --> 00:44:20,242
We had a few drinks, she got drunk
and fell asleep like you see.

589
00:44:20,282 --> 00:44:24,202
You’re lying. You’re doing to May
the same thing you did to Win, right?

590
00:44:24,242 --> 00:44:25,802
What is she talking about?

591
00:44:27,762 --> 00:44:29,042
- Wanneung
- Meedee

592
00:44:29,082 --> 00:44:30,562
I told you to wait.
Why didn’t you?

593
00:44:30,602 --> 00:44:32,402
Because you were late.

594
00:44:33,162 --> 00:44:34,162
May.

595
00:44:38,402 --> 00:44:39,962
This is my room,

596
00:44:40,002 --> 00:44:42,162
not some marketplace.

597
00:44:42,562 --> 00:44:43,802
If you leak May’s clip

598
00:44:43,802 --> 00:44:45,082
like you did with Win,

599
00:44:45,082 --> 00:44:46,122
you’ll be in big trouble.

600
00:44:46,402 --> 00:44:49,242
Don’t you know how powerful
Meedee’s father is?

601
00:45:09,322 --> 00:45:11,322
I would like to withdraw
from this film.

602
00:45:11,322 --> 00:45:13,042
Then all the news will end.

603
00:45:13,042 --> 00:45:15,602
But I ask that Wanneung
can continue acting in this film.

604
00:45:15,722 --> 00:45:16,842
Wanneung...

605
00:45:17,202 --> 00:45:19,322
must be very important to you.

606
00:45:32,302 --> 00:45:34,782
(Wellness Medical Hospital)

607
00:45:55,822 --> 00:45:57,622
Honestly, Wanneung.

608
00:45:58,342 --> 00:46:00,462
I told you to wait.
Why didn’t you?

609
00:46:01,102 --> 00:46:03,222
I was worried about May.

610
00:46:03,222 --> 00:46:05,102
I was afraid something
might happen to her.

611
00:46:05,462 --> 00:46:06,862
Why are you worried about her?

612
00:46:06,862 --> 00:46:08,102
Are you two close?

613
00:46:09,982 --> 00:46:11,182
Well…

614
00:46:11,302 --> 00:46:13,062
Not really.

615
00:46:13,502 --> 00:46:14,502
But...

616
00:46:14,542 --> 00:46:15,862
But what?

617
00:46:17,462 --> 00:46:20,662
I feel kind of guilty toward her.

618
00:46:20,862 --> 00:46:24,302
It feels like I stole
the person she loves.

619
00:46:25,462 --> 00:46:27,862
I'm sorry, Meedee.

620
00:46:29,102 --> 00:46:31,302
That's so like you, Wanneung.

621
00:46:31,502 --> 00:46:34,062
Doing something crazy like this.

622
00:47:24,942 --> 00:47:26,502
Where did she go?

623
00:47:38,302 --> 00:47:39,462
You...

624
00:47:40,382 --> 00:47:41,582
Sit up slowly.

625
00:47:45,302 --> 00:47:46,382
I...

626
00:47:46,422 --> 00:47:48,102
How did I end up here?

627
00:47:49,302 --> 00:47:51,382
You were probably drugged
and passed out.

628
00:47:51,902 --> 00:47:54,942
Wanneung was the one
who got you out of your manager's condo.

629
00:47:56,102 --> 00:47:57,502
P'Waanwaan...

630
00:47:59,142 --> 00:48:01,582
She called me to talk about the news.

631
00:48:02,222 --> 00:48:04,942
Then she gave me something to drink.

632
00:48:04,982 --> 00:48:07,022
After that, I remember nothing.

633
00:48:07,662 --> 00:48:08,902
Could it be...

634
00:48:08,982 --> 00:48:11,502
she tried to do to me
what she did to Win?

635
00:48:12,462 --> 00:48:14,062
Wanneung said the same thing.

636
00:48:15,502 --> 00:48:16,862
But don't worry.

637
00:48:17,462 --> 00:48:20,022
My father has already handled everything.

638
00:48:20,622 --> 00:48:21,662
Why?

639
00:48:21,982 --> 00:48:24,222
Is your father that powerful?

640
00:48:24,462 --> 00:48:25,502
Yes.

641
00:48:30,142 --> 00:48:31,142
And...

642
00:48:31,142 --> 00:48:33,302
what does that supporting actress
have to do with this?

643
00:48:33,902 --> 00:48:36,062
That's just how Wanneung is.

644
00:48:36,182 --> 00:48:37,822
She likes helping people.

645
00:48:37,862 --> 00:48:39,462
She believes in justice.

646
00:48:40,822 --> 00:48:41,862
How annoying.

647
00:48:41,902 --> 00:48:43,142
Praising her won't help.

648
00:48:43,222 --> 00:48:45,142
She'll never turn around
and like you.

649
00:48:45,182 --> 00:48:47,542
Yeah, I know.

650
00:48:47,662 --> 00:48:49,622
You should thank her instead.

651
00:48:49,982 --> 00:48:52,382
If Wanneung hadn't gone
to help you,

652
00:48:52,422 --> 00:48:54,382
you definitely wouldn't have made it.

653
00:48:56,582 --> 00:48:57,742
What about you?

654
00:48:57,782 --> 00:48:59,222
Why did you help me?

655
00:48:59,422 --> 00:49:00,702
Didn't you say...

656
00:49:00,942 --> 00:49:02,862
we were just
a one- night stand?

657
00:49:07,702 --> 00:49:09,422
If I see someone in trouble,

658
00:49:09,502 --> 00:49:11,182
I'll help them.

659
00:49:11,822 --> 00:49:13,782
Don't get the wrong idea.

660
00:49:16,342 --> 00:49:18,982
If you're worried,
just say you're worried.

661
00:49:19,102 --> 00:49:21,262
Why do you have to act tough?

662
00:50:02,742 --> 00:50:03,982
Wanneung.

663
00:50:06,222 --> 00:50:07,502
Wanneung.

664
00:50:13,982 --> 00:50:16,342
Win, you're back?

665
00:50:16,382 --> 00:50:19,862
I called you so many times,
but you never answered.

666
00:50:20,262 --> 00:50:22,182
I went to talk with P’Tong today.

667
00:50:22,262 --> 00:50:24,182
I had something important to deal with,

668
00:50:24,742 --> 00:50:26,862
so I didn't want to answer yet.

669
00:50:27,142 --> 00:50:28,262
P’Tong the film director?

670
00:50:28,302 --> 00:50:29,662
What did you talk about?

671
00:50:34,862 --> 00:50:35,902
By the way, Win.

672
00:50:35,902 --> 00:50:38,062
I just helped May earlier.

673
00:50:40,582 --> 00:50:42,182
This is our time.

674
00:50:42,622 --> 00:50:44,182
Let's not talk about other people.

675
00:50:46,422 --> 00:50:48,822
If not about other people, then...

676
00:50:48,982 --> 00:50:50,542
what do you want to do?

677
00:50:56,462 --> 00:50:57,622
Win.

678
00:50:57,622 --> 00:50:59,102
You're getting a call.

679
00:51:02,542 --> 00:51:03,982
I'll answer it later.

680
00:51:07,942 --> 00:51:09,342
Win.

681
00:51:12,542 --> 00:51:13,862
Win.

682
00:51:41,422 --> 00:51:42,742
Hello, Meedee.

683
00:51:42,862 --> 00:51:44,702
Wanneung, something happened.

684
00:51:44,742 --> 00:51:47,782
May asked me to tell you
to check Win's Facebook.

685
00:51:49,462 --> 00:51:50,542
Okay, okay.

686
00:51:58,182 --> 00:52:00,382
I would like to announce
my retirement from the entertainment industry

687
00:52:00,422 --> 00:52:02,622
by withdrawing from the film
I was cast in,

688
00:52:02,662 --> 00:52:05,862
and I am willing to pay
all damages according to the contract.

689
00:52:08,062 --> 00:52:10,942
I would like to thank all my fans
for your support.

690
00:52:10,982 --> 00:52:13,102
and for always supporting me.

691
00:52:14,982 --> 00:52:16,422
Thank you.

692
00:52:28,022 --> 00:52:29,222
What did you say?

693
00:52:29,222 --> 00:52:30,942
Say that again.

694
00:52:32,262 --> 00:52:34,662
I would like to withdraw
from this film.

695
00:52:34,942 --> 00:52:36,422
Then all the news will end.

696
00:52:37,182 --> 00:52:40,022
But I ask that Wanneung
can continue acting in this film.

697
00:52:41,182 --> 00:52:43,822
Win, you've already signed the contract.

698
00:52:43,822 --> 00:52:45,382
There is also a penalty.

699
00:52:45,422 --> 00:52:48,422
And most importantly,
we're about to start filming.

700
00:52:49,742 --> 00:52:51,702
I'm sorry, P'Tong.

701
00:52:51,742 --> 00:52:53,822
for always causing you trouble.

702
00:52:57,982 --> 00:52:59,742
But I've thought this through.

703
00:53:00,382 --> 00:53:03,342
If I withdraw,
everything will end.

704
00:53:03,622 --> 00:53:06,742
As for the penalty,
please don't worry. I can pay it.

705
00:53:07,942 --> 00:53:10,982
But I ask that Wanneung
can continue acting in this film.

706
00:53:11,542 --> 00:53:14,342
This film really means
a lot to Wanneung.

707
00:53:18,542 --> 00:53:19,662
Wanneung...

708
00:53:20,382 --> 00:53:22,542
must be very important to you.

709
00:53:23,862 --> 00:53:25,942
For you to give up
everything like this.

710
00:54:00,382 --> 00:54:02,622
What exactly happened?

711
00:54:10,422 --> 00:54:12,262
(P'Waanwaan)

712
00:54:14,982 --> 00:54:16,182
Hello.

713
00:54:16,382 --> 00:54:18,382
Wanneung, just you wait.

714
00:54:18,382 --> 00:54:21,062
How could you do this to me,
you ungrateful person?

715
00:54:21,302 --> 00:54:22,782
You sent someone to attack me.

716
00:54:22,822 --> 00:54:24,302
What did Meedee's father do to you?

717
00:54:24,342 --> 00:54:26,022
What happened?

718
00:54:26,262 --> 00:54:28,502
- P'Waanwaan
- Don't meddle in my business.

719
00:54:28,542 --> 00:54:29,662
Worry about yourself.

720
00:54:29,702 --> 00:54:32,582
Now Win believes
you never truly loved her.

721
00:54:32,622 --> 00:54:33,982
You only wanted the benefits.

722
00:54:34,262 --> 00:54:35,422
Win is stupid.

723
00:54:35,462 --> 00:54:37,262
She believed the audio clip

724
00:54:37,262 --> 00:54:38,302
I edited was real.

725
00:54:39,982 --> 00:54:41,062
Don't!

726
00:54:41,062 --> 00:54:42,062
P'Waanwaan!

727
00:54:42,102 --> 00:54:44,502
Sis! Sis! Sis!

728
00:57:49,622 --> 00:57:51,822
How could you run off
on a trip alone like this?

729
00:57:51,822 --> 00:57:53,102
I won't accept that.

730
00:57:53,102 --> 00:57:56,942
Someone like you would never date anyone
just for benefits, right?

731
00:57:57,262 --> 00:57:58,982
Win Pawee.

732
00:57:59,022 --> 00:58:01,662
We'll hold hands like this
and walk forward together.

733
00:58:01,662 --> 00:58:02,982
You'll never fall.

734
00:58:03,022 --> 00:58:04,742
Because I'll always
be there to support you.

735
00:58:04,742 --> 00:58:06,382
Whenever you turn around,

736
00:58:06,382 --> 00:58:07,542
you'll always find me.

737
00:58:07,542 --> 00:58:10,302
If becoming a superstar
is my dream,

738
00:58:10,302 --> 00:58:10,782
then you

739
00:58:10,782 --> 00:58:12,422
are something even more precious than that.

740
00:58:12,422 --> 00:58:13,742
Believe me,

741
00:58:13,742 --> 00:58:17,102
you'll be my present
and my future.

742
00:58:17,342 --> 00:58:18,382
Win.

743
00:58:19,702 --> 00:58:21,742
- Oh, just now...
- That wasn't good.

744
00:58:21,982 --> 00:58:24,622
The moment it stuck on...
Oops, it went through.

745
00:58:30,942 --> 00:58:33,102
- You're late.
- All done.

746
00:58:33,942 --> 00:58:35,742
She wouldn't stop kissing me.

747
00:58:37,382 --> 00:58:38,622
(Too shy)

748
00:58:41,982 --> 00:58:43,262
Win.

749
00:58:43,302 --> 00:58:44,302
Cut.

750
00:58:44,422 --> 00:58:46,142
Good thing I didn't shower this morning.
